headline: Review & Preview: Fed’s Big Finale
summary: The moment Wall Street has spent the last six weeks waiting for has nearly arrived: The Federal Reserve will make its final interest-rate decision of the year at 2 p.m. ET tomorrow.  Traders see an 87.4% chance that the Federal Open Market Committee will opt for a quarter-point cut, according to the CME FedWatch Tool.  Such odds fell to about 30% in November but rebounded in the wake of dovish commentary from key central bank officials like New York Fed President John Williams.
